review_blob:
Coffee flavor seamlessly blends with ipa. Coffee is big in the aroma and dominates the first taste of this fine beverage.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Aleman / Two Brothers / Stone DayMan Coffee IPA

review_blob: Rich aroma. Coffee, bourbon darker flavors richly blend together. A great beer.
Sweet malt combined with full hop bite balances well. Very nice. Reminds me of Dales Deviant
Earthy almost peaty hop aroma. Beautiful orange copper with full head. Nice balance of hop and malt flavor. A cool experiment from Mikkeller.
beer_name: Mikkeller Single Hop Nelson Sauvin IPA

review_blob: A little hay smell up front. Nice rich golden to amber color with frothy head. Complex flavor with mix of funk and spice which opened up as the beer warmed. Lively with full carbonation. Overall an enjoyable saison.
12 oz bottle. Great hop aroma up front lets you know whats comin. Definitely hop forward but with some sweetness to balance it out. Hop bite to round it out. A very good DIPA!
